                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17050668" author="daniel_sun" created="Wed, 4 Mar 2020 00:50:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The ideal solution is to make &lt;tt&gt;?[&lt;/tt&gt;  become a real operator, the side effect of the solution is that it may break existing code, e.g. &lt;tt&gt;true?&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;2&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;, but will not break &lt;tt&gt;true ? &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; : &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;2&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;. Actually the latter is the recommended code style for ternary expression.&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
                            <comment id="17050669" author="daniel_sun" created="Wed, 4 Mar 2020 00:53:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is the workaround. Remember we can always eliminate ambiguities with parentheses.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;true ? (&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;quot;abc&amp;quot;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; as String[]) : new String&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17051605" author="emilles" created="Wed, 4 Mar 2020 20:41:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is it reasonable to back out of safe indexing until this is looked into further?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
